The White House released a statement expressing sadness over the death of Tim Hetherington, a film director and photographer, who was killed while working in Misrata, Libya. The statement also expressed concern for other journalists who were wounded alongside him. It emphasized the importance of journalists' work in keeping the public informed and holding leaders accountable. The statement called on the Libyan government and all governments worldwide to take measures to protect journalists. The United States pledged to provide assistance to the injured journalists in getting the necessary care. The statement concluded by expressing sympathy for the journalists and their families.